    "rag_evidence": [
      {
        "content": "Price oracle uses spot reserves enabling flash-loan manipulation\n\nLending market prices collateral from a Uniswap V2 pair's spot reserves (getReserves) instead of a TWAP. An attacker flash-loans, skews the pool, borrows against inflated collateral, and repays \u2014 extracting value. This is an external-call/oracle dependency bug: the contract trusts an externally controllable price source. Fix: use a manipulation-resistant TWAP or Chainlink feed with staleness checks.",
        "doc_id": "code4rena-oracle-spot-price-manipulation",
        "chunk_id": 0,
        "total_chunks": 1,
        "metadata": {
          "protocol": "Lending",
          "date": "2023-06-02",
          "vuln_type": "external_call",
          "severity": "high",
          "loss_usd": 0,
          "chain": "ethereum",
          "url": "https://code4rena.com/reports",
          "source": "code4rena",
          "chunk_id": 0,
          "total_chunks": 1,
          "doc_id": "code4rena-oracle-spot-price-manipulation"
        },
        "score": 0.03306010928961749
      },
      {
        "content": "Reentrancy-class drain via ERC677 transferAndCall hook\n\nBug-bounty disclosure: a lending market accepted a token implementing transferAndCall; the hook re-entered the borrow flow before collateral state was finalized, enabling an over-borrow. Root cause is the same checks-effects-interactions violation as classic reentrancy but triggered by a non-standard token callback. Mitigation: nonReentrant on all state-touching entrypoints and finalize accounting before external token movement.",
        "doc_id": "immunefi-reentrancy-cream-2021",
        "chunk_id": 0,
        "total_chunks": 1,
        "metadata": {
          "protocol": "Lending",
          "date": "2021-08-30",
